{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> εὔζωνος</b>, <br /> <i>Epic dialect</i> ἐΰζ-, ον, (ζώνη) <b>well-girdled</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus (only in 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” and “hymnus ad Cererem”), as epithet of women, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.429, “hymnus ad Cererem” 255, +others \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> later, of men, <b>girt up for exercise, active</b>, μῆκος δ᾽ ὁδοῦ εὐζώνῳ ἀνδρὶ πέντε ἡμέραι ἀναισιμοῦνται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.72; τριήκοντα ἡμερέων εὐζώνῳ ὁδός [prev. work] 104, compare 2.34, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.97 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of light troops, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 5.4.23, 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 3.35.7, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Demetrius” 9 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of ὁπλῖται without their heavy shields, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 7.3.46 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: generally, <b>well-equipped</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Josh.4.13; also εὔ. τῇ κεφαλῇ πυκτεύειν 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “Philostrati majoris imagines” 2.19 \">LXX+2nd c.AD+</a>]; later, of ships, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Maximus Tyrius Sophista 1.3 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]. <i>adverb</i> -νως [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Alciphro Epistolographus 3.55. \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> of a garment, <b>well-girded</b>, uncertain in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 342. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>unencumbered</b>, πενία [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Pelopidas” 3; εὔ. καὶ ἐλεύθερος βίος 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 56.6. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> in Lit. Crit., <b>work-a-day, unpretending</b>; in depreciatory sense, <b>cheap</b>, τὸ εὔ. καὶ οἷον εὐτελὲς εἶδος τοῦ λόγου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Hermogenes Rhetor “περὶ ἰδεῶν” 2.10; τὸ εὔ. χωρὶς εὐτελείας [prev. work] 1.11; ἐκπίπτειν τὸν λόγον εἰς τὸ -ότερον [prev. work] 1.5. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7536","accentedUnicode":"εὔζωνος","shortDef":"well-equipped","mediumDef":"well-equipped","stepGloss":"well-equipped","stepTransliteration":"euzōnos","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}